despite the stiff grass.

1.2. Shifting Force-Dynamic Patterns At this point, another factor can be added-change through time-and with it, the steady-state force-dynamic patterns give rise to a set of change-ofstate patterns. In one type of these, the Antagonist, rather than impinging

FORCE DYNAMICS

